==================================================
ABUSE / SUSPICIOUS BEHAVIOR DETECTION
==================================================

Flag users for:

- excessive API usage
- scraping-like behavior
- repeated bulk exports
- repeated failed logins
- unusual download patterns
- many accounts from same IP
- many companies from same user
- unusually high AI costs
- mass proposal generation
- suspicious payment behavior
- usage inconsistent with plan limits

==================================================
SUSPICIOUS BEHAVIOR FLAGS
==================================================

Examples:

{
  "flag_type": "excessive_exports",
  "severity": "medium",
  "reason": "User exported 500 opportunities in 1 hour",
  "recommended_action": "Review account"
}

{
  "flag_type": "ai_cost_spike",
  "severity": "high",
  "reason": "User generated $90 AI cost in one day on Starter plan",
  "recommended_action": "Temporarily restrict AI generation"
}

==================================================
PLAN LIMIT ENFORCEMENT
==================================================

Track limits by plan:

STARTER:
- limited watchlists
- limited AI summaries
- limited proposal drafts
- limited historical searches

PRO:
- higher limits
- more watchlists
- proposal generation
- historical intelligence

AGENCY:
- team accounts
- bulk analysis
- higher AI limits
- advanced analytics

Admin should be able to override limits manually.

